The Netflix series “Self Made: Inspired by the Life of Madam C.J.
Walker, widely documented to have been America’s first self-made female millionaire, made her fortune building an Indianapolis-based beauty products company that served black women across the U.S. and overseas.
Walker’s Gospel of Giving: Black Women’s Philanthropy during Jim Crow” and speaking about her to audiences around the country for years.
While viewers will enjoy the series, I want them to learn that Walker didn’t just live a life of hard-won opulence.
She exemplified black women’s generosity.